{
  "text": "IgG subclass proteins were isolated by affinity chromatography on a protein ASepharose CL-4B (Pharmacia Fine Chemicals, Uppsala, Sweden) column [CITATION_1] . In brief, IgG3 was obtained by passing IgG solution through the column. IgG2 and IgG1 were isolated by pH gradient elution of the protein A-bound IgG (hereafter referred to as IgGl-rich IgG). Their purities were tested by Gm typing.",
  "citation_candidates": [
    "20450614",
